sect2.sect3:
Introduction to Xorg AMDGPU Driver
The Xorg AMDGPU Driver package contains the X.Org Video Driver for newer AMD Radeon video cards starting from Volcanic Islands. It can also be used for Southern and Sea Islands if the experimental support was enabled in the kernel.
&lfs83_checked;
For Direct Rendering to work, you need to enable the radeonsi Gallium driver at build time. Also, all cards require Firmware to be available when the kernel driver is loaded. Firmware can be obtained from . See below for additional firmware.
